I would bid 2S. You are not going to get doubled in 2S. The opponents
have nothing in spades to double you with and both opponents have
minimums. Also, the opponents don't have x-ray vision so they don't
know if you could be more distributional.

Partner is marked with a little something since RHO passed the 1H
response and LHO didn't take a bid over your reopening 1S bid.. There
is no reason why partner can't have something modest such as:
S 10x   H xxxx  D xx  C Kxxxx. You would love your chances to make 2S
on a diamond lead. Also, the opponents  might make a defensive mistake
such as RHO trying to cash his heart ace from H Ax trying to get a
heart ruff. Please note, partner is not going to play you for a 20
count and he is most likely going to pass 2D.

But even if 2S is not making there is no reason why some LHO's might
take the push to 3D as either a possible make or a good sacrifice
against 2S. If 3D makes you got an average.  If 3D goes down you
probably have close to a top.

Even if 2S is down one and you are left to play it there for -100  it
is possible 3D might make for -110.

And then there is the possibilty the defense is inaccurate.

With so many possibilities of  getting a better score, I can't
possibly imagine passing at pairs.
You don't win pairs events by being a mouse.

Eric Leong
