According to your first entry you stated that the hand would be
somewhat above the 17-19 HCP range, but you did not like doubling
followed by 2NT. In fact it is perfect for this range.

I suggest you have a look at

http://www.gg.caltech.edu/~jeff/#bridge

To cite from there:

``knr'' computes Edgar Kaplan and Jeff Rubens' (K&amp;R) complex computer
count, published in an article in The Bridge World
...
Reiterating some of Rubens' article, this evaluator is supposed to
represent Edgar Kaplan's (very fine) hand evaluation judgment.
...
I have found it useful in mediating evaluation disagreements, and for
tuning my hand evaluation skills.

End of quote.

You can also find a link to the K&amp;R evaluation algorithm there in
text.

So it is in fact the other way round. The computer program was created
to mimic Edgar Kaplan's judgment at the table.
It allows you to compare your judgement with his.

